=begin
  conundrum.lic - automated solver for the "Conundrum" maze event in
  Zephyra Wilds (Mistwarden Temple).

  v3 changes based on real-world testing:
  - Room.current.id returns nil/unusable for unmapped Zephyra Wilds
    rooms, which is why the script hung after entering the maze (the
    room-change check `Room.current.id != previous_room_id` was always
    comparing nil to nil). Switched to Room.current_or_new.id, fetched
    once per confirmed arrival and cached in $current_room rather than
    re-queried repeatedly, in case repeated calls aren't stable.
  - Replaced passive "wait for an Obvious paths line to drift by" with
    an explicit `look` command after every move/kick, used as the
    deterministic signal that a room's data has fully arrived. Falls
    back to sending `look` itself if nothing shows up within 10s.
  - Regex for exits now matches both "Obvious paths:" and the
    "Obvious exits:" wording confirmed from testing.
  - Movement and kicking now share one `attempt_transition` primitive
    so both get the same retry/blocked/unchanged handling.

  WORKFLOW
  --------
  1. Enter the maze via the Nyessemian Arena Magister.
  2. Listen for the floating spherical guide to announce needed parts,
     and proactively poll `ask guide about status` when idle.
  3. DFS-explore the maze, recording which room contains which loot
     items, and the room-to-room exit graph as we go - rebuilt fresh
     every run since the maze re-randomizes per entry.
  4. When a needed part is located, travel there, confirm its #ID via
     live GameObj.loot, then BFS-pathfind back to the Inner Shrine and
     `kick #ID <direction>` one room at a time along that path.
  5. Repeat until all known parts are delivered.

  STATUS: WIP. Outstanding: confirm Room.current_or_new.id stability
  across repeat calls in the same room, confirm real monster-attack
  text (only have "clatters in" and the kick-denial line so far), and
  whether "out"/"in" exits mid-maze are safe to wander through.
=end
